  "texts": [
    "They used two datasets to support their findings.",
    "The first dataset consisted of 1427 X-ray images, including 224 COVID-19 cases, 700 cases of common bacterial pneumonia, and 504 normal cases.",
    "The second dataset comprised 1442 images, with 504 normal cases, 714 cases of viral and bacterial pneumonia, and 224 confirmed COVID-19 cases.",
    "Comparative analysis of various CNN models, including Xception, VGG19, Inception, MobileNet v2, and Inception ResNet v2, resulted in the best performance.",
    "When comparing MobileNet v2 and VGG19, the accuracy, sensitivity, and specificity were 98.75% for the 2-class classification and 93.48% for the 3-class classification, with sensitivity and specificity values of 92.85% and 98.75%, respectively."
